The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, March 24, 2004 				 Mercury soars as fans go still
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Examinees for Higher Secondary 2004, slated to begin on April 1, had a trying time with their revisions on Tuesday, with the mercury shooting up and intermittent power cuts all day.																								With the days temperature fluctuating between 36 degrees and 38 degrees Celsius, snags in the CESC system disrupted power supply in many areas, like Kankurgachhi and Maniktala.																								Jyotirmoy Mukherjee, president, West Bengal Council for Higher Secondary Education, sent out an appeal to power minister Mrinal Banerjee to ensure uninterrupted supply in the city and districts till the exams are over. The minister has promised to take adequate steps, Mukherjee said.
